This paper deals with information extraction from clinical texts using natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms such as Conditional Random Fields (CRF) and Support Vector Machines (SVM), which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which are commonly used in sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with numerical attribute extraction, which can be related to sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
